<p>There are two main typefaces used across the University website: <a href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/PT+Sans">PT Sans</a> and <a href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/PT+Serif">PT Serif</a>. Both are freely available from <a href="https://fonts.google.com/">Google Fonts</a>.</p>


<h3>Primary typeface</h3>

<p>The University of St Andrews' primary typeface for web is <b>PT Sans</b>. This typeface must be used for body text and headings. The common equivalent typeface available on all computers is Arial. The CSS font stack should look like this:</p>

<pre style="margin-bottom: 2em;"><code>font-family: "PT Sans",Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;</code></pre>

