<h3>Secondary typeface</h3>

<p>The University of St Andrews' secondary typeface for web is <b>PT Serif</b>. This typeface must be used only for <a href="../category-header/index.html">category header</a> sections and body text on <a href="../long-form-sections/index.html">long-form</a> pages. The common equivalent typeface available on all computers is Georgia.  The CSS font stack should look like this:</p>

<pre style="margin-bottom: 2em;"><code>font-family: "PT Serif",Georgia,"Times New Roman",Times,serif;</code></pre>

